de.boereck.matcher.eager

Interface EagerMatchable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - must be the same type as the class implementing the interface!

    public interface EagerMatchable<T>
    Can be implemented by classes that want to be able to provide matching as methods directly available on instances. Implementing classes may provide own implementations of the default methods and own implementations of the returned eager matchers.

    The disadvantage of this interface is that subclasses of the implementing class can only match on the super type

    Another use of this interface is to call method matchable(Object) to pass an object around that allows matching on a wrapped object.
